Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the noon close in Manila.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index decreased 0.7 percent
to 4,340.27, its first loss in six days.  NiHAO Mineral Resources International Inc. (NI)  , an
explorer and miner, declined 3.7 percent to 3.41 pesos, falling
from the highest since January, after the company said it sold
200 million pesos ($4.71 million) of shares at a discount to
raise funds for asset purchases. NiHAO sold 100 million shares
at 2 pesos each to President Jerry Angping, a stock-exchange
filing showed.  Roxas Holdings Inc. (ROX)  , the nationâ€™s biggest producer
of raw sugar, climbed 5.9 percent to 2.70 pesos, the sharpest
gain since Aug. 4. The company said it will export raw sugar to
 South Korea  and Japan, the first time in five years that it will
ship to markets other than the U.S.  To contact the reporter on this story:
